@Database CFG_NODEGLOBAL

@Index HBBS:Docs/Misc/Index.guide/MAIN

@Node Main "HBBS:Nodes/NodeGlobal"

  HBBS:Nodes/NodeGlobal < @{" ShowMe " system "run >nil: $HBBSEditor HBBS:Nodes/NodeGlobal $HBBSEditorParams"}
  =====================

  Description:

  The HBBS:Nodes/NodeGlobal file defines the setting for all the nodes
  individual setting can be overridden for each node by placing
  NodeLocal files in the Node Directories.  The NodeLocal Files
  use EXACTLY the same options as used in NodeGlobal.

  For Most Systems with 3 nodes (2 modems and one sysop node) you'd create
  one NodeGlobal file with the settings to be used by all the nodes, then
  in the NodeLocal dir for node 1(the sysop node) you'd override some
  of the settings! Clever Huh ?

  It is best to have only config items in the NodeLocal files that
  are different from the setting in the NodeGlobal file.  Then if you
  want to change an option, you have to change it in less places.

  Options:

  All Settings with a * before the option name should preferably be set in
  the appropriate @{"HBBS:Nodes/NodeX/NodeLocal" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/NodeLocal.guide/MAIN} config file

  SysopAccount=<string>                  @{" More... " link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/BBSGlobal.guide/SysopAccount}

 *NodeName=<string>                      @{" More... " link NodeName}
 *NodePhone=<string>                     @{" More... " link NodePhone}
 *NodeConnectScript<path>                @{" More... " link NodeConnectScript}

  AskUserPW=<boolean>                    @{" More... " link AskUserPW}

  UseSysPW=<boolean>                     @{" More... " link UseSysPW}
  SysPW=<string>                         @{" More... " link SysPW}
  SysPWScript=<file>                     @{" More... " link SysPWScript}
  SysPWPrompt=<string>                   @{" More... " link SysPWPrompt}

 *UseNodePW=<boolean>                    @{" More... " link UseNodePW}
 *NodePW=<string>                        @{" More... " link NodePW}
 *NodePWScript=<file>                    @{" More... " link NodePWScript}
 *NodePWPrompt=<string>                  @{" More... " link NodePWPrompt}

  UserNamePrompt=<string>                @{" More... " link UserNamePrompt}
  UserPWPrompt=<string>                  @{" More... " link UserPWPrompt}

 *NodeLogFile=<file>                     @{" More... " link NodeLogFile}
 *ModemLogFile=<file>                    @{" More... " link ModemLogFile}
 *CallersLogFile=<file>                  @{" More... " link CallersLogFile}
 *DoorLogFile=<file>                     @{" More... " link DoorLogFile}

 *DoorLog=<boolean>                      @{" More... " link DoorLog}
 *UploadLog=<boolean>                    @{" More... " link UploadLog}
 *DownloadLog=<boolean>                  @{" More... " link DownloadLog}

  ChatFlag=<boolean>                     @{" More... " link ChatFlag}
  Iconified=<boolean>                    @{" More... " link Iconified}
  UseOwnScreen=<boolean>                 @{" More... " link UseOwnScreen}
  OpenWatch=<boolean>                    @{" More... " link OpenWatch}

  ScrModeID=<numeric>                    @{" More... " link ScrModeID}
  ScrHeight=<numeric>                    @{" More... " link ScrHeight}
  ScrWidth=<numeric>                     @{" More... " link ScrWidth}
  ScrDepth=<numeric>                     @{" More... " link ScrDepth}

  AccessRequired=<numeric>               @{" More... " link AccessRequired}

 *UseDevice=<boolean>                    @{" More... " link UseDevice}
  AllowNewUsers=<boolean>                @{" More... " link AllowNewUsers}

  InactivitySeconds=<boolean>            @{" More... " link InactivitySeconds}
  InactivityDisconnectOverride=<boolean> @{" More... " link InactivityDisconnectOverride}

  CheckNodeScreens=<boolean>             @{" More... " link CheckNodeScreens}

  DumpModem=<boolean>                    @{  More... " link DumpModem}


@EndNode

@Node NodeName "NodeName"

  NodeName=<string>

    E.G.

    NodeName="Sysop Only Node"
    NodeName="Private Node 1"

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    Sets the node's name, mainly to be used in bulletins and WHO doors...

@EndNode

@Node NodePhone "NodePhone"

  NodePhone=<string>

    E.G.

    NodePhone="+44 1202 417197"

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    This option should contain the node's phone number.

    Note that this information will besaved in the users keyfiles so that
    other sysops can call your board to verify the users keyfile.
    See @{"Keyfiles" link HBBS:Docs/Misc/KeyFiles.guide/MAIN}

@EndNode

@Node NodeLogFile "NodeLogFile"

  NodeLogFile=<path>

    E.G.

    NodeLogFile=HBBS:Nodes/NodeX/Logs/Node.Log

    No Default, Must Be Set

    Specifies the log file for the specific node.

    Please use the setting in the example for this option where possible.

@EndNode

@Node NodeConnectScript "NodeConnectScript"

  NodeConnectScript=<path>

    E.G.

    NodeConnectScript=HBBS:Scripts/Node1Connect.scr

    No Default

    This script will be run after a user has connected to the node, this script
    is run BEFORE the user is asked for the following items: system password,
    node password and username/password.  Should be used for running bulletin
    generators and other such programs.

    The node will NOT wait until the script has completed before proceding with
    the rest of the login process.

    The script is called like this:

    <script name> <node number> <connect baud>

    so, using the example above, if a user connected at 38400 to node 1 the
    command that is executed by the system is this:

    HBBS:Scripts/Node1Connect.scr 1 38400

    If a user logs on locally the connect baud will be "LOCAL" so you
    can test for this in any scripts you create.

@EndNode

@Node UseSysPW "UseSysPW"

  UseSysPW=<boolean>

    E.G.

    UseSysPW=TRUE

    Default = FALSE

    This Option when enabled will ask the user for a password before the user
    can log on the the system,  this password is prompted for BEFORE the
    user is asked for the NodePassword.

@EndNode

@Node SysPW "SysPW"

  SysPW=<string>

    E.G.

    SysPW="OK"

    Default = "PASSWORD"

    Specifies the password for the system.

@EndNode

@Node SysPWScript "SysPWScript"

  SysPWScript=<path>

    E.G.

    SysPWScript=HBBS:Scripts/SysPW.scr

    No Default

    Specifies the HBBS Script to run BEFORE the user gets asked for the system
    password,  you shoud not use any references to any user details in this
    script as the user has not been asked for a username yet!

    The node waits for this script to complete before proceding.

    This script is called with the same paramaters as the @{"NodeConnectScript" link NodeConnectScript}

    Example for use:

    Use this script to create a custom system password screen file.

@EndNode

@Node SysPWPrompt "SysPWPrompt"

  SysPWPrompt=<string>

    E.G.

    SysPWPrompt="Enter System Password :"

    Default = "System PW:"

    This prompt is displayed to the user before they enter the system password
    if enabled. See @{"UseSysPW" link UseSysPW}

@EndNode

@Node UseNodePW "UseNodePW"

  UseNodePW=<boolean>

    E.G.

    UseNodePW=TRUE

    Default = FALSE

    This Option when enabled will ask the user for a password before the user
    can log on to the node they have called.  This option is great for private
    nodes.  Can be combined with @{"UseSysPW" link UseSysPW} for ultimate protection!

@EndNode

@Node NodePW "NodePW"

  NodePW=<string>

    E.G.

    NodePW="BAD-DOOD"

    Default = "PASSWORD"

    Specifies the password for the node.

@EndNode

@Node NodePWScript "NodePWScript"

  NodePWScript=<path>

    E.G.

    NodePWScript=HBBS:Scripts/Node1PW.scr

    No Default

    Specifies the HBBS Script to run BEFORE the user gets asked for the node
    password,  you shoud not use any references to any user details in this
    script as the user has not been asked for a username yet!

    The node waits for this script to complete before proceding.

    This script is called with the same paramaters as the @{"NodeConnectScript" link NodeConnectScript}

    Example for use:

    Use this script to create a custom screen file.

@EndNode

@Node NodePWPrompt "NodePWPrompt"

  NodePWPrompt=<string>

    E.G.

    NodePWPrompt="Enter Node Password :"

    Default = "Node PW:"

    This prompt is displayed to the user before they enter the node password
    if enabled. See @{"UseNodePW" link UseNodePW}

@EndNode

@Node AskUserPW "AskUserPW"

  AskUserPW=<boolean>

    E.G.

    AskUserPW=FALSE

    Default = TRUE

    If you don't want to ask the user for a password (if you are running an
    open system) then set this option to FALSE.  You might also want to set
    the option to FALSE if this if for the sysop's local node

@EndNode

@Node CallersLogFile "CallersLogFile"

  CallersLogFile=<path>

    E.G.

    CallersLogFile=HBBS:Nodes/NodeX/Logs/Callers.Log

    No Default, Must Be Set

    Specifies the filename of the callerslog file, please use the setting
    in the example above where possible.

@EndNode

@Node DoorLogFile "DoorLogFile"

  DoorLogFile=<path>

    E.G.

    DoorLogFile=HBBS:Nodes/NodeX/Logs/Door.Log

    No Default, Must Be Set

    Specifies the filename of the DoorLog file, please use the setting
    in the example above where possible.

@EndNode

@Node DoorLog "DoorLog"

  DoorLog=<boolean>

    E.G.

    DoorLog=FALSE

    Default = TRUE

    When enabled a file will be created that details what doors were run,
    by who, at what time, and with what parameters for each node that this
    option is enabled on.

@EndNode

@Node UploadLog "UploadLog"

  UploadLog=<boolean>

    E.G.

    UploadLog=FALSE

    Default = TRUE

    When enabled the file UploadLog will be created in the node's "Logs"
    directory.

@EndNode

@Node DownloadLog "DownloadLog"

  DownloadLog=<boolean>

    E.G.

    DownloadLog=FALSE

    Default = TRUE

    When enabled the file DownloadLog will be created in the node's "Logs"
    directory.

@EndNode

@Node ChatFlag "ChatFlag"

  ChatFlag=<boolean>

    E.G.

    ChatFlag=FALSE

    Default = TRUE

    When set to FALSE the user cannot page the sysop!

    Can be overridden at when node is running by cycling the chat gadget
    between "Chat ON" and "Chat OFF"

@EndNode

@Node Iconified "Iconified"

  Iconified=<boolean>

    E.G.

    Iconified=TRUE

    Default = FALSE

    When set to TRUE and you start a node up the node window will not
    open, you'll have to click on the the node you want to see the window of in
    the listview and then on the button marked WINDOW for it to appear..

    (P.S. It's not *ACTUALLY* Iconified, it's just not OPEN! :-)

@EndNode

@Node UseOwnScreen "UseOwnScreen"

  UseOwnScreen=<boolean>

    E.G.

    UseOwnScreen=FALSE

    Default = TRUE

    When set to FALSE and you click the screen gadget to bring up the node's
    watch screen HBBS will bring up a window on the CtrlScrn instead of on a
    seperate screen, this is so that us lucky gits with 24bit gfx cards can
    have a 1280x1024*256 colour screen and display 6 node windows on one
    screen, and belive me it looks SOOOOOOOOOOOO cool! :-)

    Can be overridden at when node is running by clicking on the settings
    button on the node control panel and toggling the cycle gadget between
    "Use Window" and "Use Screen"

@EndNode

@Node OpenWatch "OpenWatch"

  OpenWatch=<boolean>

    E.G.

    OpenWatch=TRUE

    Default = FALSE

    When you start a node with this option set to TRUE the node program
    will open the watch screen or window and brings it to the front.


@EndNode

@Node UseDevice "UseDevice"

  UseDevice=<boolean>

    E.G.

    UseDevice=TRUE

    Default = FALSE

    With this option set the node will try to open a the serial device
    specified in the HBBS:Nodes/NodeX/Device file.  If set to FALSE
    the node will be treated as a local node.

@EndNode

@Node AccessRequired "AccessRequired"

  AccessRequired=<numeric>

    E.G.

    AccessRequired=100

    Default = 0

    This option specifies the mimium access lever a user must have before they
    can log onto this node.  If set to LESS than the access level for new users
    no new users will be allowed to log on.

    Generally this should be set to 0 for node 1 or your bbs and if you have
    lots of nodes and one is private for group members and sysop's then set this
    to the same level as a group member..

    Kewl huh ?

@EndNode

@Node ModemLogFile "ModemLogFile"

  ModemLogFile=<path>

    E.G.

    ModemLogFile=HBBS:Nodes/NodeX/logs/Modem.Log

    No Default, Must Be Set

    Specifies the log file for the specific node.

    Please use the setting in the example for this option where possible.

@EndNode


@Node AllowNewUsers "AllowNewUsers"

  AllowNewUsers=<boolean>

    E.G.

    AllowNewUsers=YES

    Default to YES.

    If this option is disabled no new users will be able to join the system.
    Usefull if you have private nodes or too many users.

@EndNode

@Node ScrModeID "ScrModeID"

   ScrModeID=<numeric>

     E.G.

     ScrModeID=626692 ;  DBLNTSC Hi-Res Laced
     ScrModeID=32768  ;  Hi Res
     ScrModeID=32772  ;  Hi Res Laced
     ScrModeID=167936 ;  Pal: Hi Res
     ScrModeID=167940 ;  Pal: Hi Res Laced
     ScrModeID=102400 ;  NTSC: Hi Res
     ScrModeID=102404 ;  NTSC: Hi Res Laced

     Defaults to the same setting as specified in BBSGlobal.

     This option lets you set the screenmode for the node's watch window/screen

@EndNode

@Node ScrHeight "ScrHeight"

   ScrHeight=<numeric>

     E.G.

     ScrHeight=200

     Defaults to the same setting as specified in BBSGlobal.

     Specifies the Height of the node's watchwindow screen.

@EndNode

@Node ScrWidth "ScrWidth"

   ScrWidth=<numeric>

     E.G.

     ScrWidth=640

     Defaults to the same setting as specified in BBSGlobal.

     Specifies the Width of the node's watchwindow screen.

@EndNode

@Node ScrDepth "ScrDepth"

   ScrDepth=<numeric>

     E.G.

     ScrDepth=4

     Defaults to the same setting as specified in BBSGlobal.

     Sets the amount of bitplanes for the node's watch window screen,
     one bitplane = 2 colours, for every extra bitplane the amount of
     colours double. so for a 4 Colour screen it would be set to 2,
     an eight colour screen would be 3 and so on..

@EndNode

@Node UserNamePrompt "UserNamePrompt"

  UserNamePrompt=<string>

    E.G.

    UserNamePrompt=Please Enter Your Handle >

    No Default, Must be set.

    Specifies the prompt that will be used when asking for a users handle.

@EndNode

@Node UserPWPrompt "UserPWPrompt"

  UserPWPrompt=<string>

    E.G.

    UserPWPrompt=Please Enter Your Password >

    No Default, Must be set.

    Specifies the prompt that will be used when asking for a users password.

@EndNode


@Node InactivityDisconnectOverride "InactivityDisconnectOverride"

  InactivityDisconnectOverride=<boolean>

    E.G.

    InactivityDisconnectOverride=TRUE

    Defaults to FALSE

    Use this on a node if you want inactivity disconnect to be disabled.
    For example on a LOCAL node this might be useful

    See Also: InactivitySeconds

@EndNode

@Node InactivitySeconds "InactivitySeconds"

  InactivitySeconds=<numeric>

    E.G.

    InactivitySeconds=60

    Defaults to 120 seconds

    If the BBS is sat at a command prompt (using Get_Line() only) for more
    than the amount of seconds specified here the user will be logged off.

@EndNode

@Node CheckNodeScreens "CheckNodeScreens"

  CheckNodeScreens=<boolean>

    E.G.

    CheckNodeScreens=NO

    Defaults to YES

    If set to NO the node won't check <nodepath>/Screens/Special when searching
    for screens

@EndNode

@Node DumpModem "DumpModem"

  DumpModem=<boolean>

    E.G.

    DumpModem=YES

    Defaults to NO

    Dumps all commands sent to the modem to a new window

@EndNode


